[thinking] **Considering TCK agent performance**
[thinking] 
[thinking] The TCK agent runs before the native image generation to create necessary metadata, which includes resource access. That seems fine. But what about testing under the native image? The `doReport` method sets system output properties to a large size. It also calls another method, `doReportWhich`. If `org.apache.env.Which` isn’t available, it simply prints an output. If it is available, there shouldn’t be any issues. I’ll need to keep these details in mind for effective testing.
